value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast VPNl&d1 (Ito et al., 2010; Yu et al., 2010). There are approximately 23 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast BLVp2 (VLPl&p1). Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. A neurite projects medially through the ring and crosses the midline. Another branch projects to the lateral junction.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast BLVp2 (VLPl&p1) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). It has its soma lateral to the brain (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) list aIP-g and pIP-e as corresponding to the Yu et al. (2010) pIP6, with pIP-e additionally corresponding to pIP5.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast WEDa2.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron of the aIP-h cluster in the anterior inferior protocerebrum, which comprises approximately 11 neurons (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior subesophageal ganglion.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron of the aSG-a cluster, which consists of approximately 10 neurons (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Stated to be a descending clone in Cachero et al. (2010) Table 1, but VNC projections not shown in supplement.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad1. Its cell bodies located are located in the pars intercerebralis. Projections extend laterally away from the pars intercerebralis and then ventrally to the lateral junction. The extensive arbors span the arch, lateral junction and the medial ring. The axonal arbors are likely to be enriched in the lateral junction. Females have less extensive arbors compared with males.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless-expressing neuron that develops from the SMPad1 neuroblast (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). It has its soma in the pars intercerebralis and projects laterally, arborizing in the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010). There are approximately 23 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad2. Its cell bodies are located in the dorsal pars intercerebralis. Neurites project ventroposteriorly and then bifurcate. One branch projects ipsilaterally and terminates in the medial protocerebrum. The other branch projects ventromedially, turns dorsally at the midline and then joins the path of the same cluster on the contralateral side possibly arborizing in the contralateral hemisphere. The dendritic arbors are likely to be located in the lateral junction while the axonal arbors are in the ventral medial protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast SMPad2 (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 10 of these cells per hemisphere, with their somas in the pars intercerebralis (Lee et al., 2000; Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Correspondence of Yu et al. (2010) - FBrf0211884 aSP1 to aSP1 in other studies is unclear - they also seem to call this aSP2-p in fig S2 and give contradictory correspondences in table S1. and Cachero et al. (2010) list Yu et al. (2010) aSP1 as possibly corresponding to aSP-b and aSP-c.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SMPad4.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast SMPad4 (Ito et al., 2013). There are approximately 3 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Slight discrepancy here, in that SMPad4 clones only found to contain 2 neurons in Ito et al. (2013), but possible that these were only partial clones.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DALcm1 (CREa2).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DALcm1 (CREa2) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 50 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) map Kimura et al. (2008) AL4 to aSP-d, but Yu et al. (2010) map AL4 to their aSP3.

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the anterior superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010). It has terminals in the superior intermediate and medial protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Arborization regions determined from Cachero et al. (2010) data in Virtual Fly Brain.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anterior superior protocerebrum. Neurites project ventrally in the dorsal lateral protocerebrum and form arbors extending down to the lateral crescent.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless aSP-f neuron of the female. It has sex-specific arborization in a female-enlarged region of the superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010; Kohl et al., 2013).

A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPal2. The cell bodies are located away from the neuropil, lateroanteriorly from the lateral horn. A neurite enters a neuropil tract anterior to lateral horn and projects medially to arborize in the dorsolateral protocerebrum. It also projects to the contralateral hemisphere.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless aSP-g neuron of the female. It has sex-specific arborization in a female-enlarged region of the superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010; Kohl et al., 2013). It receives input in the lateral horn and integrates sensory information of multiple modalities, including taste and smell (Taisz et al., 2023). It also has arborization outside of the lateral horn and an axon that crosses the midline (Taisz et al., 2023). There are approximately 11 of these cells per hemisphere and they can be divided into three morphological subtypes (Taisz et al., 2023).
A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DPLal2 (LHl2).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the adult female anterior superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 5 of these per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010). It has sex-specific arborization in a female-enlarged region of the superior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010; Kohl et al., 2013).

A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv3. Its cell bodies are located ventrally to the anterior optic tubercle. Neurites project medially to arborize in the ipsilateral anterior optic tubercle. Arborization localizes to the dorsal region of the anterior optic tubercle. A neurite also branches to cross the midline in a distinctive V shape to arborize in the contralateral anterior optic tubercle.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron derived from the DALcl1 (AOTUv3) neuroblast (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). It has its cell body ventral to the anterior optic tubercle (AOTU) and it arborizes in a dorsal region of the AOTU in both hemispheres (Yu et al., 2010). It receives input from LC10a neurons in the AOTU (Nojima et al., 2021).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast AOTUv4.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DALcl2 (AOTUv4) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 26 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) map Yu et al. (2010) - FBrf0211884 aSP12 to aSP-j, but Yu et al. (2010) map aSP12 to aDT-d.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast LHl1. The cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. The neurites first curve ventrally before entering a tract in neuropil region below lateral horn, then projects medially forming arborizations in the region medial to the lateral horn.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron of the female with its cell body lateral to the lateral horn, dendritic arborization in the lateral horn and axonal projections to the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010). It receives input in the wedge and outputs onto and inhibits the female doublesex pMN2 (vpoDN) neuron (Wang et al., 2021). Most of its synaptic terminals are in the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010; Baker et al., 2022). A projection also extends across the midline (Yu et al., 2010; Baker et al., 2022). It preferentially responds to male sine song, rather than pulse song (Baker et al., 2022). There are approximately 20 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Wang et al. (2020) - FBrf0247919 states that aSP-k neurons are probably a subset of vpoIN. Based on Hemibrain data, all these (aSP8) cells cross the midline, so probably correspond to the 'commissural' subset of vpoIN neurons, AVLP_pr02, in Baker et al. (2022) - FBrf0254226.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPav2. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. A neurite makes a distinct turn, travels on the surface of the neuropil around the lateral horn to the posterior superior lateral protocerebrum to form broad superficial web-like arborizations in the superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum. A neurite also crosses the midline and arborizes in a small region at the medial end of the contralateral superior medial and intermediate protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast SLPav2 (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). It has its cell body located anteroventral to the lateral horn, almost on the surface of the ventrolateral protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010). The neurite makes a distinct turn, travels on the surface of the neuropil around the lateral horn to the posterior superior lateral protocerebrum to form broad superficial web-like arborizations in the posterior superior medial protocerebrum (PSMP) (Yu et al., 2010). It also crosses the midline and arborizes in a small region at the medial end of the contralateral PSMP (Yu et al,. 2010). There are approximately 24 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast SLPa&l1.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast SLPa&l1 (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 6 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the lobula.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma just posterior to the lobula plate (Yu et al., 2010). It has its dendrites in the lobula plate and axonal arborization in the lateral posterior brain (Yu et al., 2010). There are approximately 30 of these cells per hemisphere (Kimura et al., 2008).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the medulla.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body superficial to the ventral medulla and local arborization in the medulla (Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: Kimura et al. (2008) only found these in males, but Yu et al. (2010) show them also in females.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast PSp3. Its cell bodies are located laterally in a cluster close to the tract entrance below the protocerebral bridge. A neurite projects anteriorly before branching. The dorsal branch leads to dense arborizations in the ventral and medial ipsilateral ring. The dorsal projection travels lateroventrally forming dense arborizations in multiple regions including the lateral accessory lobe, posterior antennal mechanosensory motor center and subesophageal zone before exiting the brain. In the ventral nerve cord, the projections travel along a lateral tract and arborize mostly in the meso- and metathoracic neuromeres. This clone is rare in females.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DL2 (CP3) (Ren et al., 2016) and has its cell body in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (Yu et al., 2010). In the brain, it has arbors in the lateral protocerebral complex (Yu et al., 2010). It descends to the ventral nerve cord, where it has presynaptic terminals in all three thoracic neuromeres (Cachero et al., 2010; Yu et al., 2010). There are approximately 3 of these cells per hemisphere (Ren et al., 2016).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) report 6 cells per hemisphere.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNp1. The cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. A neurite projects ventrally, arborizing in the dorsal anterior lobula. The neurite then fasciculates with the great commissure to terminate in the contralateral lobula.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located between the lateral superior protocerebrum and the optic lobe (Yu et al., 2010). It projects ventrally, arborizing in the dorsal anterior lobula then follows the great commissure to the contralateral lobula (Yu et al., 2010). It develops from neuroblast VPNp1 (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). There are approximately 24 of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNp&v1. Its cell bodies are located in the lateral cell body region. Neurites are likely to project to a region in the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). It develops from neuroblast BLP2 (VLPp1) (Ito et al., 2013; Yu et al., 2013). These neurons show no gross sexual dimorphism (Cachero et al., 2010).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) say that pIP3 and pIP7 from Yu et al. (2010) are morphologically distinct subtypes of pIP-c.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast VPNd2.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the lateral brain (Kimura et al., 2005). It develops from neuroblast VPNd2 (Ito et al., 2013).

A clone of neurons in the adult female brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DL1. The cell bodies are located in the posteriolateral brain. Neurites project anteriorly forming arbors in the entire ring and regions ventral to the ring. One branch projects medially and crosses the midline.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DL1 (CP2) (Ren et al., 2016) and has its cell body in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 20 of these cells per hemisphere (Ren et al., 2016).

definition.value: pC2 has been listed as an exact synonym for this in the past, but pC2 is actually a partially overlapping class of doublesex-expressing neurons (Rideout et al., 2010 - FBrf0210397), which now has its own class - FBbt:00047350. Cachero et al. (2010) report 34 cells per hemisphere. Cachero et al. (2010) list pIP-e as corresponding to the Yu et al. (2010) pIP5/6 and aIP-g also corresponding to pIP6.

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its soma in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult brain that expresses fruitless, all of which develop from neuroblast DM5.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by MARCM using a fru-GAL4 driver (FBal0276838), with clones induced at the first instar larval stage (Cachero et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron that develops from neuroblast DM5 (Ren et al., 2016) and has its cell body in the posterior inferior protocerebrum (Cachero et al., 2010). There are approximately 12 of these cells per hemisphere (Ren et al., 2016).

definition.value: Cachero et al. (2010) only report 6 cells per hemisphere.

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp36 (female)

value.value: Adult female fruitless neuron that develops from the first intermediate neural progenitor to form from neuroblast DM6 during the larval stage (Ren et al., 2016). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Cachero et al., 2010; Ren et al., 2016) and it is part of the pMP-f cluster (Ren et al., 2016).
